ing VFS reachable is a positive step.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test adjustments**\\n\\nI could add test assertions to include all stubs, like importing VFS and VisitorAttributes, and maybe even using a lambda for VirtualFileVisitor, though that might not be necessary. If the class isn’t included, then ClassLoader.loadClass requires metadata. Native testing should pass after generating metadata, but I wonder about the Forge workflow—does it run tests with the agent and then use the generated metadata? Since we don't run tests, I could still adjust VfsUtilsTest to reference VFS and VisitorAttributes directly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_t5mZ6gper7p04MxoN4yGNZml|fc_0bf2ba5f4d8f26120169f9b736997881a0972523f3f8da5d5f", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2947, "output": 593, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36308, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777973034189, "responseId": "resp_0bf2ba5f4d8f26120169f9b72ac7f481a0994f4b9748da6a4f"}}
